8 // ----
9 // This pass is responsible for finalizing the functions frame layout, saving ----
10 // callee saved registers, and for emitting prolog & epilog code for the ----
11 // function. ----
12 // ----
13 // This pass must be run after register allocation. After this pass is ----
14 // executed, it is illegal to construct MO_FrameIndex operands. ----
15 // ----
16 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
17 ----

524 /// registers. ----
525 static void updateLiveness(MachineFunction &MF) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
526 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
527 // Visited will contain all the basic blocks that are in the region ----
528 // where the callee saved registers are alive: ----
529 // - Anything that is not Save or Restore -> LiveThrough. ----
530 // - Save -> LiveIn. ----

532 // The live-out is not attached to the block, so no need to keep ----
533 // Restore in this set. ----

535 SmallVector WorkList; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

541 ----
542 if (Entry != Save) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
543 WorkList.push_back(Entry); 0

546 Visited.insert(Save); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

549 if (Restore) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
550 // By construction Restore cannot be visited, otherwise it ----
551 // means there exists a path to Restore that does not go ----
552 // through Save. ----
553 WorkList.push_back(Restore); 0
554 ----
555 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
556 const MachineBasicBlock *CurBB = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0

726 /// Compute which bytes of fixed and callee-save stack area are unused and keep ----
727 /// track of them in StackBytesFree. ----
728 static inline void ----
729 computeFreeStackSlots(MachineFrameInfo &MFI, bool StackGrowsDown, 0
730 unsigned MinCSFrameIndex, unsigned MaxCSFrameIndex, ----
731 int64_t FixedCSEnd, BitVector &StackBytesFree) { ----
732 // Avoid undefined int64_t -> int conversion below in extreme case. ----
733 if (FixedCSEnd > std::numeric_limits::max()) 0
734 return; 0
735 ----
736 StackBytesFree.resize(FixedCSEnd, true); 0
737 ----
738 SmallVector AllocatedFrameSlots; 0
739 // Add fixed objects. ----
740 for (int i = MFI.getObjectIndexBegin(); i != 0; ++i) 0
741 // StackSlot scavenging is only implemented for the default stack. ----
742 if (MFI.getStackID(i) == TargetStackID::Default) 0
743 AllocatedFrameSlots.push_back(i); 0
744 // Add callee-save objects if there are any. ----
745 if (MinCSFrameIndex <= MaxCSFrameIndex) { 0
746 for (int i = MinCSFrameIndex; i <= (int)MaxCSFrameIndex; ++i) 0
747 if (MFI.getStackID(i) == TargetStackID::Default) 0
748 AllocatedFrameSlots.push_back(i); 0
749 } ----
750 ----
751 for (int i : AllocatedFrameSlots) { 0
752 // These are converted from int64_t, but they should always fit in int ----
753 // because of the FixedCSEnd check above. ----
754 int ObjOffset = MFI.getObjectOffset(i); 0
755 int ObjSize = MFI.getObjectSize(i); 0
756 int ObjStart, ObjEnd; ----
757 if (StackGrowsDown) { 0
758 // ObjOffset is negative when StackGrowsDown is true. ----
759 ObjStart = -ObjOffset - ObjSize; 0
760 ObjEnd = -ObjOffset; 0
761 } else { ----
762 ObjStart = ObjOffset; 0
763 ObjEnd = ObjOffset + ObjSize; 0
764 } ----
765 // Ignore fixed holes that are in the previous stack frame. ----
766 if (ObjEnd > 0) 0
767 StackBytesFree.reset(ObjStart, ObjEnd); 0
768 } ----
769 } 0

771 /// Assign frame object to an unused portion of the stack in the fixed stack ----
772 /// object range. Return true if the allocation was successful. ----
773 static inline bool scavengeStackSlot(MachineFrameInfo &MFI, int FrameIdx, 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
774 bool StackGrowsDown, Align MaxAlign, ----
775 BitVector &StackBytesFree) { ----
776 if (MFI.isVariableSizedObjectIndex(FrameIdx)) 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
777 return false; 0
778 ----
779 if (StackBytesFree.none()) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
780 // clear it to speed up later scavengeStackSlot calls to ----
781 // StackBytesFree.none() ----
782 StackBytesFree.clear(); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
783 return false; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
784 } ----
785 ----
786 Align ObjAlign = MFI.getObjectAlign(FrameIdx); 0
787 if (ObjAlign > MaxAlign) 0
788 return false; 0
789 ----
790 int64_t ObjSize = MFI.getObjectSize(FrameIdx); 0
791 int FreeStart; ----
792 for (FreeStart = StackBytesFree.find_first(); FreeStart != -1; 0
793 FreeStart = StackBytesFree.find_next(FreeStart)) { 0
794 ----
795 // Check that free space has suitable alignment. ----
796 unsigned ObjStart = StackGrowsDown ? FreeStart + ObjSize : FreeStart; 0
797 if (alignTo(ObjStart, ObjAlign) != ObjStart) 0
798 continue; 0
799 ----
800 if (FreeStart + ObjSize > StackBytesFree.size()) 0
801 return false; 0
802 ----
803 bool AllBytesFree = true; 0
804 for (unsigned Byte = 0; Byte < ObjSize; ++Byte) 0
805 if (!StackBytesFree.test(FreeStart + Byte)) { 0
806 AllBytesFree = false; 0
807 break; 0
808 } ----
809 if (AllBytesFree) 0
810 break; 0
811 } ----
812 ----
813 if (FreeStart == -1) 0
814 return false; 0
815 ----
816 if (StackGrowsDown) { 0
817 int ObjStart = -(FreeStart + ObjSize); 0
818 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "alloc FI(" << FrameIdx << ") scavenged at SP[" 0
819 << ObjStart << "]\n"); ----
820 MFI.setObjectOffset(FrameIdx, ObjStart); 0
821 } else { ----
